    "content_hash": "58fdc0b87ddecff0",
    "department": "Data Analytics and AI",
    "description": "At Snowflake, we are powering the era of the agentic enterprise. To usher in this new era, we seek AI-native thinkers across every function who are energized by the opportunity to reinvent how they work. You don’t just use tools; you possess an innate curiosity, treating AI as a high-trust collaborator that is core to how you solve problems and accelerate your impact. We look for low-ego individuals who thrive in dynamic and fast-moving environments and move with an experimental mindset — who rapidly test emerging capabilities to discover simpler, more powerful ways to deliver results. At Snowflake, your role isn't just to execute a function, but to help redefine the future of how work gets done.\n\nSnowflake is hiring a Principal Analyst, GTM Analytics within the Data Analytics and AI org (DAA). This role will serve as the dedicated analytics partner for the Services Delivery (SD) organization, owning the data strategy, reporting, and analytical frameworks that drive visibility into SD operations, project delivery, and use case outcomes. You will be responsible for ensuring our data infrastructure is accessible across multiple surfaces—from executive dashboards to autonomous AI agents—directly boosting the productivity of our Field and Delivery teams.\n\nThis role requires in-person attendance in either our Menlo Park (CA), Dublin (CA), Bellevue (WA), or New York (NY) office at least 3 days per week.\n\n\n\nIN THIS ROLE YOU WILL:\n\n - Certify the Foundation: Own the development of \"Gold Standard\" analytical data models (via dbt) for Services Delivery. You will ensure every metric—from billable utilization to project margins—is accurate, governed, and ready for both executive reporting and AI consumption.\n\n - Translate Business Logic to AI Models: Act as the lead translator between Services leadership and technical systems. You will take complex business rules (e.g., revenue recognition patterns or resource leveling logic) and implement them into AI-friendly data models that power predictive tools.\n\n - Build for Multi-Surface Accessibility: Architect data infrastructure that isn't just for dashboards. You will ensure our Services data is structured to be accessible across multiple surfaces—whether it’s a Streamlit app, a Slack bot, or an autonomous AI agent.\n\n - Drive AI Self-Service \u0026 Productivity: Directly boost the productivity of our global delivery team by providing \"Natural Language\" data solutions. You will enable business users to query complex project data themselves using AI-driven interfaces, reducing the reliance on manual ad-hoc reporting.\n\n - Ensure Data Excellence: Manage the technical reconciliation between CRM/PSA systems (Salesforce) and internal data models to ensure 100% data integrity across all reporting surfaces.\n\n - Measure the Transformation: Develop and lead the measurement framework for our AI initiatives. You will conduct deep-dive analyses to prove how AI is changing our delivery speed, quality, and margins, providing the data-backed narrative for our services evolution.\n\n - Bridge the Gap: Partner closely with Analytics Engineering, Product, and the wider DAA team to ensure the \"plumbing\" of our data infrastructure supports the high-velocity needs of a global Services Delivery organization.\n   \n\n\nOUR IDEAL CANDIDATE WILL HAVE:\n\n - Technical Mastery: 10+ years of experience in Analytics/BI within large-cap tech companies or high-growth SaaS environments; featuring expert-level SQL and hands-on dbt proficiency for production-grade data modeling.\n\n - AI \u0026 Infrastructure Literacy: Deep understanding of how to build \"AI-ready\" data structures—specifically for LLM consumption and agentic interfaces—using Python and data app frameworks like Streamlit.\n\n - Services Domain Expertise: Deep familiarity with Professional Services or Consulting operations and the CRM/PSA ecosystem (e.g., Salesforce). You have a firm grasp of the \"Resource-to-Revenue\" lifecycle and the technical data structures required to measure global delivery.\n\n - Strategic Leadership: The ability to navigate high-level strategy with executives while remaining \"hands-on-keys\" to build solutions and lead the technical roadmap.\n\n - Elite Communication: Proven ability to translate complex technical architectures and data deep-dives into clear, actionable narratives for non-technical stakeholders.\n\nEvery Snowflake employee is expected to follow the company’s confidentiality and security standards for handling sensitive data. Snowflake employees must abide by the company’s data security plan as an essential part of their duties. It is every employee's duty to keep customer information secure and confidential.\n\nSnowflake is growing fast, and we’re scaling our team to help enable and accelerate our growth. We are looking for people who share our values, challenge ordinary thinking, and push the pace of innovation while building a future for themselves and Snowflake.\n\nHow do you want to make your impact?\n\nFor jobs located in the United States, please visit the job posting on the Snowflake Careers Site for salary and benefits information: careers.snowflake.com http://careers.snowflake.com",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
    "is_active": true,
